what is javascript 
=> javascript is a light weight, cross-platforf and interpreted compiled programming language which is also known as the scripiting language for webpages.

=> it is also known as object-based scripiting language.

=> it is well-known for the development of web pages, many non-browser environments also use it.

=> in 1993, Mosaic , the first popular web browser came into existence. In the year 1994, Netscape was founded by Marc Andreesen.

=>Javascript firt name was livescript.

=> due trademark and other reason livescript was renamed as javascript.

=> Pure Javascript code is also known as vanila javascript.

=>Javascript is used to create interactive websites. It is mainly used for:
-Clinet side validation
-Dynamic drop-down menus
-Displaying date and time
-Displaying pop-up windows and dialog boxes (like an alert dialog box, confirm dialog box and prompt dialog box)
-Displaying clocks etc.

=> It is written in < script > tag.

=>< script > tag is written in between < head > or < body > tag.

Example:-
< script > 
       document.write("hello javascript by javascript");
< /script >

=> where a document object represnts the HTML documnet that is displayed in that window.write() is a function to display your content.

=>There are three ways to add javascript in file:-
(1)Inline -add using event
(2)Internal -in < script > tag in < body > or < head > tag
(3)External -create new file using javascript extension and add with < script > tag in html file.